example.statement:
What if instead we tweaked the function in the previous example to be 

	g(x) = \begin{cases}\dfrac{x-1}{x^2-1} \amp x\neq 1 \\ 2 \amp x = 1 \end{cases}

What will happen to the limit?  Explain your answer.

